.TH TALCULATOR 1 "April 18, 2026"
.SH NAME
talculator \- a GTK3 based scientific calculator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B talculator
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
This manual page gives a short description of
.B talculator
and documents its command line arguments.
.br
\fBtalculator\fP is a GTK3 based calculator with basic and scientific modes.
It supports algebraic notation and RPN (Reverse Polish Notation), plus paper
mode, different number bases (decimal, hexadecimal, octal, and binary), and
angle bases (radian, degree, and grad). Arithmetic evaluation is powered by
libqalculate (arbitrary precision). Further features include arithmetic
operations plus precedence handling, trigonometric functions, power, square
root, natural and common logarithm, constants (e, PI, user defined), memory,
inverse and hyperbolic functions, and user defined functions.
Typed expression input uses strict identifier validation.

.SH OPTIONS
.B
talculator
accepts the following options:	
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show summary of options.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Show version of program.

.SH FILES
.TP
~/.config/talculator/talculator.conf
Automatically generated configuration file for
.B
talculator
.TP
~/.talculator
Legacy fallback configuration location.

